The '''XP-38 sport landspeeder''' was a [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub]] [[Landspeeder/Legends|landspeeder]].

==History==
It was similar in design to the earlier [[X-34 landspeeder/Legends|X-34]]; in fact, it looked much like a slim version of this older model. Its engines were similar to those of the [[Seraph-class urban landspeeder|Flash speeders]] of [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]].

This updated, sleeker model was a popular civilian speeder, and was also often used by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] forces as a support vehicle at planetary garrisons.

The XP-38 was released shortly before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], and customers soon found that its repulsorlift system made travel over rough terrain quite difficult. SoroSuub produced new versions (i.e. the [[XP-38 All-Terrain Roughrider]]) for use in rural areas.<ref name="TNEGtVV">''[[The New Essential Guide to Vehicles and Vessels]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
[[Kenner Products|Kenner]] intended to release a very different-looking version of an XP-38 landspeeder as part of its never-released ''[[The Epic Continues]]'' toy line. Intended to be [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] personal speeder, it was said to feature "upgraded Ion thrusters, improved defense capabilities and auto droid navigation control."<ref name="SWCA">{{WebCite|url=http://theswca.com/index.php?action=disp_item&item_id=50984|text=1985-86 Line Extension Presentation Binder Page 26 - XP-38 Landspeeder|work=The Star Wars Collectors Archive|archivedate=20161118020559}}</ref>

